        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2019-06-05 14:09:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nInteresting way to test for fs encryption. I did for ARM this:\n\nAC_DEFUN([LB_FS_ENCRYPTION_ENABLED], [\nLB_CHECK_COMPILE([if generic file system encryption exist],\nfscrypto, [\n       #include <linux/fscrypt.h>\n],[\n       int tmp = FS_KEY_DERIVATION_NONCE_SIZE;\n],[\n       LB_CHECK_CONFIG_IM([FS_ENCRYPTION], [], [\n               AC_DEFINE(CONFIG_LDISKFS_FS_ENCRYPTION, 1, [enable encryption for ldiskfs])\n       ])\n],[\n       AC_DEFINE(CONFIG_LDISKFS_FS_ENCRYPTION, 1, [enable encryption for ldiskfs])\n])\n]) # LB_FS_ENCRYPTION_ENABLED\n\nWhich way is better?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "30c4262a331ea5759c605d73fc3ecca1a7d425c7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 353,
        "name": "Li Dongyang",
        "email": "dongyangli@ddn.com",
        "username": "lidongyang"
      },
      "date": "2019-06-06 05:44:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nJames, it's done this way to make it work with distros like sles12.\nFirst we should make LDISKFS_FS_ENCRYPTION consistent with the config\nfrom kernel. But on sles12, with i_crypt_info inside ext4_inode_info,\nwe have to enable it because the way we generate the Makefile for\nldiskfs.ko.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "8f9bb2b18cda0b95e34f1047beebb9e9cbeef2b2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2019-06-07 03:50:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nis this supposed to work? When I built this for testing purposes, cannot mount ldiskfs:\n\n # /home/green/git/lustre-release/lustre/utils/mkfs.lustre --mgs --fsname=lustre --mdt --index=0 --param=sys.timeout=20 --param=lov.stripecount=-1 --param=mdt.identity_upcall=/home/green/git/lustre-release/lustre/utils/l_getidentity --backfstype=ldiskfs --device-size=250000 --mkfsoptions=\"-O ea_inode\" --reformat /tmp/lustre-mdt1 \n\n   Permanent disk data:\nTarget:     lustre:MDT0000\nIndex:      0\nLustre FS:  lustre\nMount type: ldiskfs\nFlags:      0x65\n              (MDT MGS first_time update )\nPersistent mount opts: user_xattr,errors=remount-ro\nParameters: sys.timeout=20 lov.stripecount=-1 mdt.identity_upcall=/home/green/git/lustre-release/lustre/utils/l_getidentity\n\nformatting backing filesystem ldiskfs on /dev/loop0\n\ttarget name   lustre:MDT0000\n\tkilobytes     250000\n\toptions        -I 1024 -i 2560 -q -O ea_inode,dirdata,uninit_bg,^extents,dir_nlink,quota,huge_file,flex_bg -E lazy_journal_init -F\nmkfs_cmd = mke2fs -j -b 4096 -L lustre:MDT0000  -I 1024 -i 2560 -q -O ea_inode,dirdata,uninit_bg,^extents,dir_nlink,quota,huge_file,flex_bg -E lazy_journal_init -F /dev/loop0 250000k\n   Invalid filesystem option set: ea_inode,dirdata,uninit_bg,^extents,dir_nlink,quota,huge_file,flex_bg\nmkfs.lustre FATAL: Unable to build fs /dev/loop0 (256)\nmkfs.lustre FATAL: mkfs failed 256",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
